{
  "document_id": "job-34",
  "title": "Job 34",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-heading-elihu-proclaims-god’",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Elihu Proclaims God’s Justice"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Then Elihu continued and said:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“Hear my words, you wise men,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "for the ear tests words"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "Let us choose what is right;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "For Job has said, ‘I am innocent,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "in spite of being right I am counted a liar;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "Who is there like Job,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "who goes in company with evildoers"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "For he has said, ‘It profits one nothing"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "“Therefore, hear me, you who have sense;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "For according to their deeds he will repay them,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "Of a truth, God will not do wickedly,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Who gave him charge over the earth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "If he should take back his spirit to himself"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "all flesh would perish together,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "“If you have understanding, hear this;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Shall one who hates justice govern?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "who says to a king, ‘You scoundrel!’"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "who shows no partiality to nobles,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "In a moment they die;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "“For his eyes are upon the ways of mortals,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "There is no gloom or deep darkness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "For he has not appointed a time for anyone"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "He shatters the mighty without investigation"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Thus, knowing their works,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "He strikes them for their wickedness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "because they turned aside from following him"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "so that they caused the cry of the poor to come to him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "When he is quiet, who can condemn?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "so that the godless should not reign"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "“For has anyone said to God,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "teach me what I do not see;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "Will he then pay back to suit you"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "Those who have sense will say to me,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "‘Job speaks without knowledge;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "Would that Job were tried to the limit,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-34-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "For he adds rebellion to his sin;"
    }
  ]
}